text: Not right now, the only one you’d ever be able to grab would be the “Primary color” at the top because that’s the only ‘named’ value. The rest are an undefined list of up to 19 colors, so no way to directly request {{ brand_color_4 }} because that may or may not exist depending on how many the customer set.

Now what we could do (I’ll need to check with <@ULCSUPTGU> and team) is make it so you can load in the set of brand default colors into a color picker field in a custom module you create, allowing the front-end user to select a color that comes from their brand default colors. In that scenario you as the developer wouldn’t be requesting a specific one, instead you’d be listing out the brand colors in your module which would dynamically populate based on that customer’s defaults
